    "rich_text_97Y9PE": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "settings": {
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h4>Step 1. Measure and Prepare the Gate Opening</h4><ul><li>Use our <a href=\"/pages/how-to-measure-for-wooden-gates\" title=\"How to Measure for Wooden Gates\">How to Measure</a> page to calculate the size of your opening and what hinges will work for you.</li></ul><h4>Step 2. Install Gate Posts</h4><ul><li>Mark post positions on both sides of the opening, ensuring they are the correct width apart for your gate and hinges.</li><li>Dig holes at least 600mm - 750mm deep - deeper for heavier gates and if the soil is softer.</li><li>Set posts plumb (vertically straight) and level using a spirit level.</li><li>Fix in place with Post Mix or concrete and allow to set for 48 hours before hanging your gates, whilst bracing the posts to prevent movement. </li></ul><h4>Step 3. <strong>Attach Hinges to the Gate</strong></h4><ul><li>Lay the gate flat on the ground and position the hinges along the edge of the gate, about 100mm from top and bottom.</li><li>Drill pilot holes and attach the adjustable hook and band hinges to the gate using appropriate screws or bolts</li></ul><h4>Step 4. <strong>Fit the Gate to the Posts</strong></h4><ul><li>Lift the gate into position. Hold the gate at the desired height (50-75mm from the ground) and mark where the hinges will attach to the posts.</li><li>Install the hook plates (if you're using adjustable hinges) onto the gate posts, ensuring they are level with each other.</li><li>Fix the hook plates to the posts securely, leaving enough room for the hinges to slide into place.</li><li>Slide the hinges onto the hook plates to hang the gate, ensuring it swings freely and doesn't rub against the posts. </li></ul><h4><strong>Step 5. Check Swing and Alignment</strong></h4><ul><li>Open and close the gate to ensure smooth movement.</li><li>Adjust the hinge bolts if the gate sags or needs levelling.</li><li>Check gaps between the gate and posts - typically 10-20mm for swing clearance.</li></ul><h4><strong>Step 6. Fit Latch, Drop Bolt and Throwover Loop (if needed)</strong></h4><ul><li>Latch - position and fix at a comfortable height.</li><li>Drop Bolt - Fix to the gate that closes second, ensuring it drops cleanly into the ground or socket - for double gates.</li><li>Throwover Loop - Fix to the top of the primary gate (the gate that closes first) to secure both gates when shut - for double gates. </li></ul><h4><strong>Step 7. Final Checks</strong></h4><ul><li>All fixings are tight</li><li>Gates open and close smoothly</li><li>No excessive gaps or binding</li><li>Apply <a href=\"https://www.ruby-group.co.uk/products/uv-protection-oil\" title=\"https://www.ruby-group.co.uk/products/uv-protection-oil\">Osmo Oil</a></li></ul>",
